# Car Thing Release Rule

**MANDATORY:** Every time you make changes to car-thing as a result of a user prompt, you MUST build and push to GitHub. Every single time. No exceptions.

```bash
./car-thing/scripts/commit-and-release.sh [optional-commit-message]
```

Run this script immediately after completing car-thing edits. Do not wait for the user to ask. Do not skip it.

The script:
1. Commits car-thing and bridge changes
2. Pushes to origin (dotfiles)
3. Subtree-pushes app to deskthing (8utl3r/deskthing)
4. Builds and creates a GitHub release

If no car-thing changes exist, the script exits without error. You may omit the message; it will use version + date.
